    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "claim": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-worst-case",
    "type": "Claim",
    "name": "CFD model correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump",
    "description": "The CFD hemolysis model, employing the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law damage model with SST k-omega turbulence closure, correctly ranks the relative hemolysis index (RH) across all five flow-speed operating conditions (3, 4, 5, 6, 7 L/min at 2400 RPM) for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. The claim asserts that the model-predicted worst-case condition (5 L/min, 2400 RPM) matches experimentally observed worst-case hemolysis, and that RH values remain below 1.0 relative to the predicate device across the full operating envelope. This claim supports the regulatory submission decision that component dimensional tolerances do not elevate hemolysis risk beyond the predicate benchmark.",
    "purpose": "Support regulatory acceptance of CFD-based hemolysis worst-case identification in lieu of exhaustive experimental matrix testing for dimensional tolerance variations.",
    "scope": "Valid for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry at MRL 2, Class II CPB indication, within the operating envelope defined by 3–7 L/min flow rate and 2400 RPM impeller speed."
  },
